<subSubSection pageId="115" pageNumber="116" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="115.[189,454,1321,1347]" box="[189,454,1321,1347]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,454,1321,1347]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,454,1321,1347]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="115.[189,1399,1369,1543]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,372,1369,1395]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="versa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,372,1369,1395]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">Cheilosia versa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[378,468,1370,1396]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[818,960,1369,1396]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavigena" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[818,960,1369,1396]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">C. flavigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[967,1059,1370,1396]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but differs by having yellow pilosity on mesonotum (vs yellow and black in 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[735,876,1406,1432]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavigena" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[735,876,1406,1432]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">C. flavigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[883,976,1406,1433]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), presence of pilosity also on ventral part of face (vs only latero-dorsally in 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[658,802,1443,1469]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavigena" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[658,802,1443,1469]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">C. flavigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[810,906,1443,1469]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), basoflagellomere smaller and distinctly darkened antero-dorsally (vs larger in size and completely orange in 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[974,1113,1480,1506]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavigena" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[974,1113,1480,1506]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">C. flavigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1120,1212,1480,1506]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), and bristles on scutellum margin shorter than length of scutellum (vs longer or almost as long in 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[1142,1284,1516,1543]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavigena" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1142,1284,1516,1543]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">C. flavigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1291,1386,1517,1543]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="115.[188,1399,1584,1721]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,369,1584,1610]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="versa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,369,1584,1610]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">Cheilosia versa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[375,464,1584,1610]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is also similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Shiraki, 1968" authorityName="Shiraki" authorityYear="1968" box="[661,1269,1584,1610]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="komabaensis" subGenus="Neocheilosia">
<emphasis box="[661,773,1584,1610]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">Cheilosia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[790,942,1584,1610]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">Neocheilosia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[957,1108,1584,1610]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">komabaensis</emphasis>
Shiraki, 1968
</taxonomicName>
(see figs in 
<bibRefCitation author="Barkalov A. V. &amp; Ichige K." box="[189,476,1620,1647]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" pagination="571 - 80" refId="ref48606" refString="Barkalov A. V. &amp; Ichige K. 2016. Review of the Asian species of the subgenus Neocheilosia Barkalov (Diptera, Syrphidae), with description of new species. Zootaxa 4150 (5): 571 - 80. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4150.5.4" type="journal article" year="2016">Barkalov &amp; Ichige 2016</bibRefCitation>
), both species have longer pile latero-dorsally on the face, but 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[1205,1302,1621,1647]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="versa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1205,1302,1621,1647]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">C. versa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1309,1399,1621,1647]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs by having pilosity in lower part of face and yellow maculae laterally on frons, and parafacia yellow pollinose. A subgeneric classification is not proposed as the taxon is described based on a single female.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="115" pageNumber="116" type="etymology">
